<div><b>STAY INFORMED: Fraser Island bushfire as at 4pm Sat 24 Oct</b></div><div><b></b></div><div><b>Bushfire warning level: ADVICE</b></div><div></div><div>Queensland Fire and Emergency Services (QFES) advises there is a bushfire at the north eastern end of Fraser Island.</div><div></div><div>You need to <b>keep up to date</b> and<b> decide what actions you will take</b> if the situation changes.</div><div></div><div>Currently as at 4pm Saturday 24 October a large bushfire is burning to the north and west of Orchid Beach as well as to the north of Dundubara and the Awinya track. The fire is travelling in a south south-easterly direction towards Dundubara. </div><div></div><div>Queensland Parks and Wildlife Service (QPWS) are continuing to monitor the fire. Travellers are advised to check the QPWS website for updates and travel advice.</div><div></div><div>People in the area will be affected by smoke, which will reduce visibility and air quality.</div><div></div><div>Properties are not under direct threat at this time. Call Triple Zero (000) immediately if you believe you or your property is under threat.</div><div></div>

<div><b>Trinity Beach – bushfire as at 9.20am Mon 26 Oct</b></div><div></div><div>Queensland Fire and Emergency Services (QFES) crews are monitoring a bushfire burning west of Paguna Street, Trinity Beach. This fire is posing no threat to property at this time. The blaze is putting out a lot of smoke, which may linger for the next few days. Residents are asked to close windows and doors and if suffering from a respiratory condition, keep medications close by. Motorists should drive with caution and to conditions. If residents are concerned their property is under threat, they are advised to call Triple Zero (000) immediately.</div>
